## Findings

- MSConfig and Advanced System Settings are essential for troubleshooting and performance management.
- Computer Management consolidates tools for scheduling, monitoring, and managing system resources.
- System Information provides comprehensive diagnostics.
- Resource Monitor offers granular real-time performance insights.
- Command Prompt remains a powerful tool for troubleshooting and system management.
- Registry Editor is critical but risky; changes must be made cautiously.
- UAC continues to provide a vital security layer.

## Mitigation / Practical Application

- Use MSConfig for diagnostics, not permanent startup management.
- Monitor page file size and configure crash dumps for troubleshooting.
- Regularly review Event Viewer logs for anomalies.
- Automate tasks with Task Scheduler.
- Apply least privilege principles with Shared Folders and Local Users/Groups.
- Monitor performance with perfmon and resmon.
- Use Command Prompt for quick troubleshooting.
- Keep UAC enabled to reduce risk of compromise.
- Avoid unnecessary registry modifications.

